---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { SITE, LEGAL } from '../consts';
---
<LegalLayout title="Affiliate Disclosure" description="How MoveWell Reviews makes money — and why it doesn't affect our reviews.">
  <p class="lead">
    {SITE.name} ({SITE.domain}) is a reader-supported publication operated by {LEGAL.entity}. In
    accordance with the U.S. Federal Trade Commission's
    <a href="https://www.ftc.gov/business-guidance/resources/disclosures-101-social-media-influencers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Endorsement Guides (16 CFR Part 255)</a>,
    we disclose the following.
  </p>

  <h2>How we earn money</h2>
  <p>
    Some links on this site are affiliate links. If you click one and make a purchase, we may earn a
    commission <strong>at no additional cost to you</strong>. These commissions help fund our testing
    and keep the site free to read.
  </p>

  <h2>Amazon Associates</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE.name} is a participant in the Amazon Services LLC Associates Program, an affiliate
    advertising program designed to provide a means for sites to earn advertising fees by advertising
    and linking to Amazon.com. <strong>As an Amazon Associate we earn from qualifying purchases.</strong>
    Amazon and the Amazon logo are trademarks of Amazon.com, Inc. or its affiliates. As required by
    the Amazon Operating Agreement, we do not display Amazon prices on this site; the current price is
    shown on Amazon when you click through.
  </p>

  <h2>Other affiliate programs</h2>
  <p>
    We also participate in other affiliate networks and programs, including but not limited to
    ShareASale, Impact, and CJ Affiliate, and we may work directly with brands in the walking pad,
    treadmill, recovery, home-gym, and wearables categories. The same standards apply to every one of
    these relationships.
  </p>

  <h2>This does not change our opinions</h2>
  <p>
    Our team selects, tests, and rates every product independently of any affiliate relationship. We
    do not accept payment in exchange for a positive review, and manufacturers do not get to see or
    approve a review before it's published. If we recommend something, it's because we believe it's
    genuinely useful — the presence of an affiliate link never changes what we say. Read our full
    <a href="/editorial-policy">Editorial Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Where you'll see disclosures</h2>
  <p>
    We place a clear and conspicuous disclosure near the top of every page containing affiliate links
    (reviews, "best of" roundups, comparison tables, and buying guides), in addition to this dedicated
    page. Outbound affiliate links are also marked with <code>rel="sponsored nofollow"</code> for
    search engines.
  </p>

  <h2>Pricing &amp; testing</h2>
  <p>
    We do not fabricate test results, and we do not display product pricing we haven't verified —
    always check the merchant's site for current, accurate pricing before purchasing. Where we state
    that we "tested" a product, the individual review describes our testing methodology.
  </p>

  <h2>Questions</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions about this disclosure, <a href="/contact">contact us</a> or email
    <a href={`mailto:${LEGAL.legalEmail}`}>{LEGAL.legalEmail}</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
